5:
Beaucy? Were you out at another
concert?
10:
Yes, it was a very informative
expedition into the field.
15:
You say that, but aren't you just
going as a fan... Eh, I guess if you're
having fun, then that's what matters.
20:
There you are, Beaucy! Did you think
I wouldn't notice this month's
Oculus? Explain yourself!
25:
Whoa, Beaucy's this month's cover
model? Dang. You look amazing.
30:
NAAHH! Mr. Producer, whose side are
you on?!
33:
Beaucy! How DARE you waltz into
Palpebra and start stealing fans on
my turf!
38:
Don't gravure idols and singing idols
cater to different audiences?
43:
Everyone's into everything
nowadays! But that doesn't mean I'll
just stand by and share my fans
with a newcomer!
47: You really wanna be petty over this?
50:
I understand why you'd have beef
with me. But I also need to make a
living to afford food and idol
merchandise.
52:
If you want to stop me, then you
know what to do. It's an ox-eat-rat
world in the idol industry, after all.
62:
Battle Royale: All Star Smash,
loading complete! No escape from
crossing fate! GO!
75:
Even if you moo-stered up more
power, you'd never be able to defeat
me.
80:
So long as I'm still breathing... You
haven't won yet!
84:
Now you're starting to irritate me. A
rat like you should know her place!
88:
I was content to leave matters
between us unsettled for a while
longer, but no more...
91: Today I will seal you all away!
96:
It's do-or-die now... And I don't
intend to go quietly!
99:
I... We... Hard Rock Magic will never,
ever... give up!
102:
A wasted effort. You, BRASS, idols...
It's time to say goodbye.
107:
That's what you think! Us
idols—we're here to stay!
112:
That's quite enough, don't you think,
Beaucy?
122:
Why did you stop me? They were as
good as minced meat.
125:
This isn't what you truly want. I can
feel your heart wavering.
127:
You see yourself in Noenne, don't
you?
136:
A long time ago, Beaucy wanted to
become a singing and dancing idol
like you.
144:
So what if I did? I've moo-ved on to
greener pastures. I'm proud of the
gravure idol I am today.
147:
Clinging to old dreams like that is for
fools.
150:
Yet a part of you still yearns for it.
You pretend not to see it, but deep
down, you know I speak true.
152:
I remember how shocked you were
when Noenne joined the BRASS
without a single song in her
repertoire.
154:
That shock only compounded when
you discovered her in another world,
in possession of newfound song and
power, despite losing in the BRASS...
159:
In other words, a part of Beaucy
wishes she could've been Noenne.
163:
Exactly. She can't help but wonder if
being a traditional idol could've
been in the cards for her, no matter
how much of a struggle it would've
been.
168:
You're wrong! This is complete and
utter bull! I have no regrets! I'll
destroy ALL idols!
172:
Then why did you pose for the
Oculus with pride?
174:
Why do you chase idols across
different worlds?
177: You know the answer, and so do I.
179:
You believe in Noenne's potential,
like a true fan waiting for her
underground idol to make it big.
195:
Impossible... The Cosmic Beasts
were supposed to be completely
sealed away!
201:
Wait, this isn't some kind of ploy to
pull a fast one on us, is it?!
205:
Beaucy, this is undeniable proof. No
matter how much you pretend
otherwise, your heart has spoken.
You don't want to put an end to
idols. You want them to thrive.
217:
And they're off, in search of new
idols.
222:
Yeah... Once they find them, another
BRASS will begin.
225:
BRASS: the Sequel. Otherwise known
as BRASSS.
231:
Is giving it another title really
necessary...
236:
Cacow, the day we made our
contract, you said that there's no
one way to be an idol.
239:
Because it's true. Whatever route
you choose, be it gravure,
underground, traditional... even as
an instrument of war... you're all
prime cuts in your own ways.
249:
Maybe this time, I'll try to be both a
gravure and traditional type idol.
Two is better than one, after all.
254:
Of course. Go do whatever your
heart desires.
260:
Hmm... What if I rebranded myself
like this...
272:
Err, I'm happy you figured yourself
out, but can I go home now?
